quotes.text: The impediment to action advances action. What stands in the way becomes the way.
quotes.author: Marcus Aurelius

quotes.text: It is not because things are difficult that we do not dare; it is because we do not dare that they are difficult.
quotes.author: Seneca

quotes.text: First say to yourself what you would be; and then do what you have to do.
quotes.author: Epictetus

quotes.text: Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts.
quotes.author: Winston Churchill

quotes.text: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
quotes.author: Steve Jobs

quotes.text: We cannot become what we want by remaining what we are.
quotes.author: Max DePree

quotes.text: Excellence is not a skill. It is an attitude.
quotes.author: Ralph Marston

quotes.text: The man who moves a mountain begins by carrying away small stones.
quotes.author: Confucius

quotes.text: He who conquers himself is the mightiest warrior.
quotes.author: Confucius

quotes.text: The master has failed more times than the beginner has even tried.
quotes.author: Stephen McCranie

quotes.text: You miss 100% of the shots you don't take.
quotes.author: Wayne Gretzky

quotes.text: It always seems impossible until it's done.
quotes.author: Nelson Mandela

quotes.text: The greater the difficulty, the more glory in surmounting it.
quotes.author: Epicurus

quotes.text: Mastery is not a function of genius or talent. It is a function of time and intense focus.
quotes.author: Robert Greene

quotes.text: The price of success is hard work, dedication to the job at hand.
quotes.author: Vince Lombardi

quotes.text: To reach a port we must sail, sometimes with the wind, and sometimes against it.
quotes.author: Oliver Wendell Holmes
quotes.source: The Autocrat of the Breakfast Table

quotes.text: What you get by achieving your goals is not as important as what you become by achieving your goals.
quotes.author: Zig Ziglar

quotes.text: The successful warrior is the average man, with laser-like focus.
quotes.author: Bruce Lee

quotes.text: I am not a product of my circumstances. I am a product of my decisions.
quotes.author: Stephen Covey
quotes.source: The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People

quotes.text: Don't watch the clock; do what it does. Keep going.
quotes.author: Sam Levenson
quotes.source: In One Era and Out the Other

quotes.text: Strength does not come from physical capacity. It comes from an indomitable will.
quotes.author: Mahatma Gandhi

quotes.text: A champion is defined not by their wins but by how they can recover when they fall.
quotes.author: Serena Williams

quotes.text: The difference between the impossible and the possible lies in a person's determination.
quotes.author: Tommy Lasorda

quotes.text: Skill is only developed by hours and hours of work.
quotes.author: Usain Bolt

quotes.text: There is no substitute for hard work.
quotes.author: Thomas Edison

quotes.text: Genius is one percent inspiration and ninety-nine percent perspiration.
quotes.author: Thomas Edison

quotes.text: The only place where success comes before work is in the dictionary.
quotes.author: Vidal Sassoon

quotes.text: Victory belongs to the most persevering.
quotes.author: Napoleon Bonaparte

quotes.text: Nothing in the world can take the place of persistence.
quotes.author: Calvin Coolidge

quotes.text: The greatest glory in living lies not in never falling, but in rising every time we fall.
quotes.author: Nelson Mandela

quotes.text: Do not wait to strike till the iron is hot; but make it hot by striking.
quotes.author: William Butler Yeats

quotes.text: I hated every minute of training, but I said, 'Don't quit. Suffer now and live the rest of your life as a champion.'
quotes.author: Muhammad Ali

quotes.text: The vision of a champion is bent over, drenched in sweat, at the point of exhaustion, when nobody else is looking.
quotes.author: Mia Hamm

quotes.text: If you're offered a seat on a rocket ship, don't ask what seat! Just get on.
quotes.author: Sheryl Sandberg

quotes.text: I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse.
quotes.author: Florence Nightingale

quotes.text: Quality is not an act, it is a habit.
quotes.author: Aristotle

quotes.text: We are what we repeatedly do. Excellence, then, is not an act, but a habit.
quotes.author: Aristotle

quotes.text: The only limit to our realization of tomorrow will be our doubts of today.
quotes.author: Franklin D. Roosevelt

quotes.text: Build your own dreams, or someone else will hire you to build theirs.
quotes.author: Farrah Gray

quotes.text: The best revenge is massive success.
quotes.author: Frank Sinatra

quotes.text: Either write something worth reading or do something worth writing.
quotes.author: Benjamin Franklin

quotes.text: Well done is better than well said.
quotes.author: Benjamin Franklin

quotes.text: I find that the harder I work, the more luck I seem to have.
quotes.author: Thomas Jefferson

quotes.text: Believe you can and you're halfway there.
quotes.author: Theodore Roosevelt

quotes.text: Don't be pushed around by the fears in your mind. Be led by the dreams in your heart.
quotes.author: Roy T. Bennett

quotes.text: If you can dream it, you can do it.
quotes.author: Walt Disney

quotes.text: The distance between dreams and reality is called action.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.text: Action is the foundational key to all success.
quotes.author: Pablo Picasso

quotes.text: Inspiration does exist, but it must find you working.
quotes.author: Pablo Picasso

quotes.text: I am always doing that which I cannot do, in order that I may learn how to do it.
quotes.author: Pablo Picasso

quotes.text: Everything you've ever wanted is on the other side of fear.
quotes.author: George Addair

quotes.text: Whether you think you can or you think you can't, you're right.
quotes.author: Henry Ford

quotes.text: Coming together is a beginning; keeping together is progress; working together is success.
quotes.author: Henry Ford

quotes.text: The secret of getting ahead is getting started.
quotes.author: Mark Twain

quotes.text: Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed by the things you didn't do than by the ones you did do.
quotes.author: Mark Twain

quotes.text: I never dreamed about success. I worked for it.
quotes.author: Estée Lauder

quotes.text: Success usually comes to those who are too busy to be looking for it.
quotes.author: Henry David Thoreau

quotes.text: The only person you are destined to become is the person you decide to be.
quotes.author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

quotes.text: Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail.
quotes.author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

quotes.text: What lies behind us and what lies before us are tiny matters compared to what lies within us.
quotes.author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

quotes.text: The future belongs to those who believe in the beauty of their dreams.
quotes.author: Eleanor Roosevelt

quotes.text: You must do the thing you think you cannot do.
quotes.author: Eleanor Roosevelt

quotes.text: The way to get started is to quit talking and begin doing.
quotes.author: Walt Disney

quotes.text: All our dreams can come true, if we have the courage to pursue them.
quotes.author: Walt Disney

quotes.text: A goal without a plan is just a wish.
quotes.author: Antoine de Saint-Exupéry

quotes.text: Success is walking from failure to failure with no loss of enthusiasm.
quotes.author: Winston Churchill

quotes.text: Life is 10% what happens to you and 90% how you react to it.
quotes.author: Charles R. Swindoll

quotes.text: Courage is not having the strength to go on; it is going on when you don't have the strength.
quotes.author: Theodore Roosevelt

quotes.text: Our greatest glory is not in never falling, but in rising every time we fall.
quotes.author: Confucius

quotes.text: The journey of a thousand miles begins with one step.
quotes.author: Lao Tzu

quotes.text: When I let go of what I am, I become what I might be.
quotes.author: Lao Tzu

quotes.text: Knowing others is intelligence; knowing yourself is true wisdom.
quotes.author: Lao Tzu

quotes.text: Do the difficult things while they are easy and do the great things while they are small.
quotes.author: Lao Tzu

quotes.text: I am not what happened to me, I am what I choose to become.
quotes.author: Carl Jung

quotes.text: Who looks outside, dreams; who looks inside, awakes.
quotes.author: Carl Jung

quotes.text: The privilege of a lifetime is to become who you truly are.
quotes.author: Carl Jung

quotes.text: What a man can be, he must be.
quotes.author: Abraham Maslow

quotes.text: One can choose to go back toward safety or forward toward growth.
quotes.author: Abraham Maslow
quotes.source: The Farther Reaches of Human Nature

quotes.text: In any given moment we have two options: to step forward into growth or step back into safety.
quotes.author: Abraham Maslow

quotes.text: The only impossible journey is the one you never begin.
quotes.author: Tony Robbins

quotes.text: Setting goals is the first step in turning the invisible into the visible.
quotes.author: Tony Robbins

quotes.text: It's not what we do once in a while that shapes our lives, it's what we do consistently.
quotes.author: Tony Robbins

quotes.text: The scariest moment is always just before you start.
quotes.author: Stephen King

quotes.text: Amateurs sit and wait for inspiration, the rest of us just get up and go to work.
quotes.author: Stephen King

quotes.text: Talent is cheaper than table salt. What separates the talented individual from the successful one is a lot of hard work.
quotes.author: Stephen King

quotes.text: I have learned over the years that when one's mind is made up, this diminishes fear.
quotes.author: Rosa Parks

quotes.text: You don't make progress by standing on the sidelines, whimpering and complaining.
quotes.author: Shirley Chisholm

quotes.text: Service to others is the rent you pay for your room here on earth.

quotes.text: I know where I'm going and I know the truth, and I don't have to be what you want me to be.
quotes.author: Muhammad Ali

quotes.text: Champions aren't made in gyms. Champions are made from something they have deep inside them.
quotes.author: Muhammad Ali

quotes.text: The moment you doubt whether you can fly, you cease forever to be able to do it.
quotes.author: J.M. Barrie

quotes.text: Do not wait; the time will never be 'just right.' Start where you stand.
quotes.author: Napoleon Hill

quotes.text: The starting point of all achievement is desire.
quotes.author: Napoleon Hill

quotes.text: Every great achievement was once considered impossible.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.text: The expert in anything was once a beginner.
quotes.author: Helen Hayes

quotes.text: Success is the sum of small efforts repeated day in and day out.
quotes.author: Robert Collier

quotes.text: Your limitation—it's only your imagination.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.text: Great things never come from comfort zones.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.text: Dream it. Wish it. Do it.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.text: Push yourself, because no one else is going to do it for you.
quotes.author: Unknown
